%2F%2Fworldview.earthdata.nasa.gov%2F%3Fv%3D64.49116547151472%2C25.4299555277525%2C81.23650026844116%2C33.3752680277525%26s%3D74.3507%2C31.558%252B77.2188%2C28.6324%26t%3D2024-11-10-T00%253A00%253A00Z%5C%22%3Espace%20agency%20NASA%3C%2Fa%3E.%20It%20shows%20location%20pins%20for%20Lahore%20in%20Pakistan's%20Punjab%20and%20New%20Delhi%2C%20with%20both%20cities%20under%20huge%20cloud%20of%20grey%20smog.%20Lahore%20-%20a%20city%20of%2014%20million%20people%20stuffed%20with%20factories%20on%20the%20border%20with%20India%20-%20regularly%20ranks%20among%20the%20world's%20most%20polluted%20cities%2C%20but%20it%20has%20hit%20record%20levels%20this%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELast%20week%2C%20live%20rankings%20by%20Swiss%20group%20IQAir%20gave%20the%20city%20a%20pollution%20index%20score%20of%201165.%20In%20New%20Delhi%20and%20neighbouring%20areas%2C%20it%20is%20hovering%20around%20350.%20An%20Air%20Quality%20Index%20(AQI)%20of%2050%20or%20below%20is%20considered%20good%20with%20little%20risk%20of%20pollution.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20hazardous%20level%20of%20pollution%20has%20forced%20authorities%20in%20Pakistan%20to%20close%20schools%20till%20November%2017%20in%20a%20bid%20to%20lower%20children's%20exposure%20to%20the%20pollution.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20Multan%2C%20another%20city%20of%20several%20million%20people%20some%20350%20kilometres%20away%2C%20the%20AQI%20level%20passed%202%2C000%20last%20week%2C%20according%20to%20news%20agency%20AFP.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccess%20to%20parks%2C%20zoos%2C%20playgrounds%2C%20historic%20monuments%2C%20museums%20and%20recreational%20areas%20has%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fpakistans-punjab-shuts-amusement-parks-museums-for-10-days-due-to-severe-smog-6977921%5C%22%3Ealso%20been%20banned%3C%2Fa%3E%20along%20with%20tuk-tuks%20with%20polluting%20two-stroke%20engines%20and%20restaurants%20that%20operate%20barbecues%20without%20filters.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20%26quot%3Bsmog%20war%20room%26quot%3B%20has%20been%20set%20up%20in%20Pakistan's%20Punjab%20province%20where%20staff%20members%20from%20eight%20departments%20work%20towards%20controlling%20burning%20of%20farm%20waste%20and%20managing%20traffic.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20mix%20of%20low-grade%20fuel%20emissions%20from%20factories%20and%20vehicles%20and%20agricultural%20stubble%20burning%20blanket%20the%20city%20each%20winter%2C%20trapped%20by%20cooler%20temperatures%20and%20slow-moving%20winds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20World%20health%20Organisation%20(WHO)%2C%20air%20pollution%20can%20trigger%20strokes%2C%20heart%20disease%2C%20lung%20cancer%20and%20other%20respiratory%20diseases.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20particularly%20punishing%20for%20children%20and%20babies%2C%20and%20the%20elderly.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20chief%20pollutant%20is%20PM2.5%2C%20the%20fine%20particulate%20matter%20that%20poses%20greatest%20risk%20to%20health.%20It%20comes%20from%20sources%20like%20the%20combustion%20of%20fossil%20fuels%2C%20dust%20storms%20and%20wildfires%2C%20and%20has%20been%20linked%20to%20asthma%2C%20heart%20and%20lung%20disease%2C%20cancer%2C%20and%20other%20respiratory%20illnesses%2C%20as%20well%20as%20cognitive%20impairment%20in%20children.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPM2.5%20travels%20deep%20into%20lung%20tissue%20where%20it%20can%20enter%20the%20bloodstream.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1731321540000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-11%2F74pblnqg_lahore-delhi-pollution_625x300_11_November_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fclimate-challenges-dont-see-borders-as-nasa-pic-shows-smog-covered-lahore-delhi-6993387%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20hazardous%20level%20of%20pollution%20has%20forced%20authorities%20in%20Pakistan%20to%20close%20schools%20till%20November%2017%20in%20a%20bid%20to%20lower%20children's%20exposure%20to%20the%20pollution.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22The%20coming%20reign%20of%20the%20only%20child%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20baby%20wearing%20a%20crown%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F672cfff3192f52589856bcef%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EiStock%3B%20Rebecca%20Zisser%2FBI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EA%20few%20years%20ago%2C%20Hallie%20Parker%20joined%20a%20WhatsApp%20group%20of%20millennial%20women%20who%20call%20themselves%20geriatric%20moms%20%E2%80%94%20almost%20all%20were%20close%20to%2040%20when%20they%20became%20parents.%20Half%20of%20them%20had%20two%20kids%2C%20including%20Parker%2C%20who%20at%2033%20was%20among%20the%20youngest.%20Half%20had%20only%20one%20kid%2C%20with%20no%20plans%20for%20more.%20But%20Parker%20was%20the%20only%20member%20in%20the%20group%20who%20is%20herself%20an%20only%20child.%20%26quot%3BIf%20you%20have%20questions%20about%20only%20children%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20volunteered%2C%20%26quot%3Byou%20can%20ask%20me.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20was%20flooded%20with%20queries.%20%3Cem%3EWere%20you%20lonely%3F%20Did%20you%20wish%20you%20had%20siblings%3F%20What%20did%20your%20parents%20do%20to%20normalize%20it%3C%2Fem%3E%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20level%20of%20anxiety%20in%20Parker's%20group%20chat%20made%20it%20clear%20that%20only%20children%20are%20still%20viewed%20as%20something%20of%20a%20demographic%20outlier%20%E2%80%94%20and%20a%20questionable%20one%20at%20that.%20Kids%20without%20siblings%20are%20seen%20as%20lonely%20brats%20who%20are%20moody%20and%20bossy%20and%20unable%20to%20play%20well%20with%20others.%20Their%20sense%20of%20entitlement%20draws%20everyone%20around%20them%20into%20mayhem%3A%20Just%20look%20at%20Harry%20Potter%2C%20Harriet%20the%20Spy%2C%20and%20Dennis%20the%20Menace.%20They're%20untethered%20and%20troubled%20in%20childhood%20(Drew%20Barrymore)%2C%20in%20early%20adulthood%20(Tiger%20Woods)%2C%20and%20especially%20in%20middle%20age%20(Elvis%2C%20Kanye).%20As%20only%20children%20become%20more%20prevalent%2C%20their%20alleged%20deficiencies%20have%20become%20generational%20shorthand%3A%20Instead%20of%20calling%20only%20children%20selfish%2C%20introverted%2C%20and%20lonely%2C%20we%20slap%20those%20labels%20on%20Gen%20Zers.%20No%20wonder%20we've%20never%20had%20an%20only-child%20president.%20In%20surveys%2C%20most%20Americans%20continue%20to%20say%20that%20the%20ideal%20family%20has%20two%20kids%20raised%20by%20married%20parents.%20Almost%20nobody%20%E2%80%94%20not%20even%20all%20of%20the%20mothers%20in%20Parker's%20group%20who%20have%20just%20one%20kid%20%E2%80%94%20aspires%20to%20have%20just%20one%20kid.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYet%20that's%20exactly%20what's%20happening.%20The%20only%20child's%20time%20has%20come.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBack%20in%201978%2C%20the%20National%20Council%20on%20Family%20Relations%20published%20a%20paper%20titled%20%26quot%3BThe%20One-Child%20Family%3A%20A%20New%20Life-Style%2C%26quot%3B%20as%20if%20it%20were%20introducing%20a%20strange%20countercultural%20phenomenon.%20At%20the%20time%2C%20about%2011%25%20of%20American%20families%20had%20just%20one%20kid.%20By%202015%2C%20that%20number%20had%20doubled%2C%20to%2022%25.%20Big%20families%2C%20meanwhile%2C%20have%20become%20as%20rare%20as%20only%20children%20once%20were.%20In%20the%20early%201980s%2C%2028%25%20of%20women%20had%20four%20or%20more%20kids.%20Thirty%20years%20later%2C%20it%20was%20just%2010%25.%20Families%20with%20one%20child%20may%20be%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pewresearch.org%2Fshort-reads%2F2015%2F05%2F08%2Fideal-size-of-the-american-family%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ethe%20least-desired%20outcome%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20when%20Americans%20envision%20their%20dream%20lives%2C%20but%20in%20reality%20they're%20the%20fastest-growing%20family%20configuration%20in%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20not%20hard%20to%20see%20why%20sibling-free%20families%20are%20increasingly%20common.%20Over%20the%20past%20half-century%2C%20the%20cost%20of%20raising%20a%20child%20has%20increased%20far%20faster%20than%20the%20average%20salary.%20American%20women%20are%20having%20kids%20later%20in%20life%2C%20leaving%20less%20time%20to%20bear%20multiple%20children.%20And%20the%20bigger-is-better%20belief%20about%20families%20that%20fueled%20the%20baby%20boom%20is%20now%20confined%20mostly%20to%20the%20deeply%20religious%20and%20the%20dramatically%20wealthy.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EIn%20some%20schoolrooms%2C%20it's%20now%20more%20noteworthy%20among%20kids%20to%20actually%20have%20a%20sibling%20than%20to%20have%20none.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20it's%20harder%20to%20foresee%20what%20the%20rise%20of%20the%20only%20child%20means%20for%20our%20future.%20Will%20more%20solo%20kids%20lead%20to%20a%20world%20run%20by%20spoiled%20brats%2C%20devoid%20of%20empathy%20and%20unschooled%20in%20the%20art%20of%20collaboration%3F%20The%20experts%2C%20surprisingly%2C%20say%20no.%20As%20the%20ranks%20of%20only%20children%20swell%2C%20their%20personal%20idiosyncrasies%2C%20social%20skills%2C%20and%20family%20dynamics%20could%20prove%20to%20be%20the%20very%20tools%20we%20need%20to%20thrive%20in%20modern%20life.%20In%20an%20America%20that%20is%20more%20divided%20than%20ever%2C%20the%20only%20child%20might%20just%20be%20what%20brings%20us%20back%20together.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3ENo%20one%20has%20done%20more%20to%20give%20only%20children%20a%20bad%20rap%20than%20Granville%20Stanley%20Hall.%20Once%20described%20as%20a%20%26quot%3BVictorian%20Dr.%20Spock%2C%26quot%3B%20Hall%20was%20America's%20OG%20psychologist%20%E2%80%94%20the%20first%20man%20to%20earn%20a%20doctorate%20in%20the%20field%20from%20Harvard.%20Employing%20a%20method%20that%20was%20more%20sketchy%20than%20scientific%2C%20Hall%20asked%20college%20professors%20to%20share%20stories%20about%20%26quot%3Bpeculiar%20and%20exceptional%20children%26quot%3B%20they%20had%20encountered.%20Simply%20because%20only%20children%20were%20mentioned%20more%20often%20than%20they%20occur%20in%20the%20general%20population%2C%20and%20he%20concluded%20that%20they%20were%20inherently%20flawed%3A%20sickly%2C%20unable%20to%20get%20along%20with%20others%2C%20with%20a%20deluded%20tendency%20to%20create%20imaginary%20companions.%20Being%20an%20only%20child%2C%20Hall%20declared%20in%201907%2C%20%26quot%3Bis%20a%20disease%20in%20itself.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20decades%20that%20followed%2C%20scores%20of%20%26quot%3Bexperts%26quot%3B%20relying%20on%20equally%20dubious%20methods%20echoed%20Hall's%20spurious%20claims%2C%20which%20seeped%20into%20the%20wider%20culture.%20Then%2C%20in%20the%201980s%2C%20a%20social%20psychologist%20named%20Toni%20Falbo%20%E2%80%94%20herself%20an%20only%20child%20%E2%80%94%20set%20out%20to%20rigorously%20test%20Hall's%20ideas%20about%20her%20kind.%20Reviewing%20141%20studies%20of%20personality%20development%20in%20only%20children%2C%20she%20found%20that%20they%20were%20virtually%20indistinguishable%20from%20children%20with%20siblings%2C%20with%20one%20notable%20exception%3A%20They%20scored%20%26quot%3Bsignificantly%20better%20than%20other%20groups%20in%20achievement%20motivation%20and%20personal%20adjustment.%26quot%3B%20That's%20right%3A%20They%20scored%20%3Cem%3Ebetter%3C%2Fem%3E.%20It's%20a%20finding%20that%20has%20been%20repeated%20many%20times%20since.%20Only%20children%20are%20not%2C%20on%20the%20whole%2C%20any%20more%20shy%2C%20entitled%2C%20or%20lonely%20than%20their%20peers%20with%20brothers%20or%20sisters.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20contrary%2C%20surveys%20have%20suggested%20that%20only%20children%20grow%20up%20learning%20to%20entertain%20themselves%20and%20solve%20their%20own%20problems.%20They%20don't%20mind%20eating%20alone.%20They're%20adept%20at%20forging%20close%20friendships%20that%20feel%20like%20family.%20Their%20comfort%20with%20being%20on%20their%20own%20may%20make%20them%20more%20unwilling%20to%20accept%20unhealthy%20relationships%3A%20One%20study%20found%20that%20only%20children%20were%20more%20likely%20to%20get%20divorced%20than%20their%20peers%20with%20siblings.%20And%20they%20tend%20to%20be%20academic%20achievers%20and%20highly%20independent%2C%20with%20high%20self-esteem.%20Only%20kids%20are%20more%20likely%20than%20other%20kids%20to%20become%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theatlantic.com%2Ffamily%2Farchive%2F2019%2F08%2Fceos-childhood-career%2F596158%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3ECEOs%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Thomas%20Edison%2C%20Jack%20Welch%2C%20Carl%20Icahn%20%E2%80%94%20all%20onlies.%20But%20their%20success%20may%20have%20more%20to%20do%20with%20income%20than%20inclination.%20Small%20families%20tend%20to%20be%20more%20educated%20and%20wealthier%2C%20which%20gives%20only%20children%20a%20double%20advantage%3A%20Their%20parents%20have%20more%20time%20and%20money%20to%20spend%2C%20and%20fewer%20kids%20to%20spend%20it%20on.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20child%20wearing%20a%20crown%20as%20a%20valedictorian%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F672d00785ec9bfa3d63c6278%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EDespite%20their%20reputation%20as%20shy%2C%20entitled%20loners%2C%20only%20children%20are%20tend%20to%20be%20independent-minded%20academic%20achievers%20with%20high%20self-esteem.%3Cp%3EiStock%3B%20Rebecca%20Zisser%2FBI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20her%20group%20chat%2C%20Parker%20tried%20to%20reassure%20the%20moms%20who%20worried%20about%20their%20only%20children.%20She%20loved%20being%20an%20only%2C%20she%20told%20them.%20Even%20as%20a%20child%2C%20she%20knew%20it%20provided%20her%20with%20more%20opportunities.%20She%20loved%20horseback%20riding%2C%20a%20hobby%20her%20parents%20never%20would%20have%20been%20able%20to%20afford%20if%20she%20had%20siblings.%20Her%20folks%20made%20sure%20she%20wasn't%20lonely%20by%20always%20allowing%20her%20to%20bring%20a%20friend%20along%20with%20them%20on%20vacation.%20And%20despite%20the%20stereotype%20that%20only%20children%20are%20spoiled%20rotten%2C%20Parker%20was%20always%20eager%20to%20share%20her%20snacks%20and%20toys%20with%20others.%20She%20grew%20up%20hearing%20stories%20about%20her%20mother's%20difficult%20pregnancy%20and%20so%20was%20not%20one%20to%20beg%20for%20a%20sibling.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENothing%20has%20accelerated%20the%20rise%20of%20only%20children%20more%20than%20delayed%20childbearing.%20American%20women%20in%20general%20are%20having%20children%20later%2C%20but%20the%20delay%20is%20most%20pronounced%20among%20the%20most%20educated.%20In%20fact%2C%20the%20single%20largest%20determinant%20of%20how%20many%20children%20a%20woman%20will%20have%20is%20her%20level%20of%20education%3A%20The%20more%20degrees%20you%20hold%2C%20the%20older%20you%20are%20when%20you%20start%20to%20have%20kids%2C%20the%20fewer%20kids%20you%20have.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20not%20just%20people%20having%20kids%20later%20%E2%80%94%20they're%20starting%20to%20%3Cem%3Ethink%20%3C%2Fem%3Eabout%20them%20later%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Anastasia%20Berg%2C%20a%20coauthor%20of%20%26quot%3BWhat%20Are%20Children%20For%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20how%20it%20turned%20out%20for%20the%20women%20in%20Parker's%20group%20chat.%20Most%20of%20them%20started%20out%20wanting%20to%20have%20more%20than%20one%20kid%20%E2%80%94%20but%20by%20the%20time%20they%20got%20around%20to%20bearing%20the%20cost%20and%20physical%20toll%20of%20having%20their%20first%2C%20they%20had%20changed%20their%20minds.%20In%20a%202021%20survey%2C%20about%20a%20quarter%20of%20parents%20who%20said%20they%20didn't%20expect%20to%20have%20more%20children%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pewresearch.org%2Fshort-reads%2F2021%2F11%2F19%2Fgrowing-share-of-childless-adults-in-u-s-dont-expect-to-ever-have-children%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ecited%20financial%20reasons%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20During%20the%20Great%20Depression%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wnycstudios.org%2Fpodcasts%2Ftakeaway%2Fsegments%2F70453-case-having-only-child%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3E23%25%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20families%20had%20just%20one%20child%3B%20it's%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eno%20coincidence%20that%20the%20baby%20boom%20took%20place%20during%20an%20unprecedented%20economic%20boom.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20average%20cost%20of%20raising%20a%20child%20in%20America%20from%20birth%20to%20age%2018%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.washingtonpost.com%2Fbusiness%2Finteractive%2F2022%2Fcost-raising-child-calculator%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3E%24310%2C000%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%202022%20%E2%80%94%20and%20double%20that%20if%20you%20factor%20in%20four%20years%20of%20full%20college%20tuition.%20What's%20more%2C%20full-time%20working%20parents%20are%20spending%20even%20more%20time%20with%20their%20children%20than%20stay-at-home%20parents%20of%20previous%20generations%20did%2C%20prompting%20the%20surgeon%20general%20to%20issue%20a%20warning%20about%20their%20stress%20levels%20and%20mental%20well-being.%20If%20you're%20already%20struggling%20to%20care%20for%20one%20kid%2C%20it's%20difficult%20to%20imagine%20having%20a%20second.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20trend%20toward%20fewer%20children%20isn't%20just%20an%20American%20phenomenon.%20Even%20in%20countries%20like%20Sweden%20and%20France%20that%20enjoy%20subsidized%20childcare%20and%20guaranteed%20parental%20leave%2C%20fertility%20rates%20are%20falling.%20%26quot%3BTrends%20of%20delay%20are%20consistent%20across%20the%20board%2C%26quot%3B%20Berg%20says.%20Even%20religious%20conservatives%2C%20who%20are%20biblically%20motivated%20to%20be%20fruitful%20and%20multiply%2C%20are%20starting%20families%20later%20and%20more%20often%20having%20only%20one%20child.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECorinne%20Lyons%20is%20someone%20who%20wants%20a%20big%20family.%20A%20public-school%20teacher%20in%20her%20hometown%20of%20Detroit%2C%20she%20grew%20up%20the%20only%20child%20of%20two%20only%20children.%20But%20unlike%20Parker's%2C%20her%20siblingless%20childhood%20wasn't%20entirely%20glorious.%20%26quot%3BI%20didn't%20grow%20up%20playing%20with%20other%20kids%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%20Her%20biggest%20birthday%20parties%20involved%20having%20cake%20and%20ice%20cream%20at%20school.%20She%20wants%20a%20different%20experience%20for%20her%20own%20children%2C%20but%20she%20feels%20like%20she%20doesn't%20have%20much%20time%3A%20She'll%20be%2036%20when%20she%20marries%20her%20fianc%C3%A9%20next%20September.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BDon't%20get%20me%20wrong%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%20%26quot%3BBeing%20an%20only%20child%20is%20amazing.%20It's%20also%20hard.%20I%20don't%20want%20to%20have%20to%20send%20my%20child%20to%20school%20for%20social%20interactions.%26quot%3B%20Even%20many%20only%20children%2C%20it%20would%20seem%2C%20aren't%20all%20that%20into%20having%20only%20children.%20But%20adult%20onlies%20are%20subject%20to%20the%20same%20trends%20(like%20later%20childbearing)%20and%20pressures%20(ahem%2C%20finances)%20that%20other%20Americans%20are.%20Lyons%20accepts%20that%2C%20despite%20her%20desires%2C%20she%20might%20end%20up%20having%20just%20one.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20what%20will%20the%20coming%20reign%20of%20the%20only%20child%20mean%20for%20America%3F%20For%20starters%2C%20only%20kids%20could%20spur%20us%20to%20build%20stronger%20communities%20and%20mend%20our%20divided%20social%20institutions.%20Without%20a%20built-in%20family%20of%20peers%20at%20home%2C%20only%20children%20learn%20to%20go%20out%20and%20build%20their%20own.%20Lyons%2C%20the%20public-school%20teacher%2C%20forged%20an%20extended%20family%20of%20friends%20in%20college%2C%20despite%20being%20a%20self-professed%20introvert.%20She%20was%20initiated%20into%20the%20Alpha%20Kappa%20Alpha%20sorority%2C%20and%20for%20nearly%2020%20years%20she%20has%20held%20her%20sorority%20sisters%20tighter%20than%20many%20people%20hold%20their%20relatives.%20%26quot%3BThese%20people%20aren't%20in%20my%20life%20because%20they%20have%20to%20be%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%20%26quot%3BThey're%20here%20because%20they%20%3Cem%3Ewant%3C%2Fem%3E%20to%20be.%20I%20am%20very%20intentional%20in%20building%20that%20bond.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOnly%20children%20could%20also%20transform%20America's%20business%20landscape.%20For%20starters%2C%20fewer%20kids%20means%20fewer%20heirs%20to%20take%20over%20family-run%20companies.%20In%20China%2C%20where%20the%20government's%20one-child%20policy%20created%20a%20generation%20of%20onlies%2C%20studies%20suggest%20that%20business%20founders%20with%20multiple%20children%20are%20significantly%20more%20likely%20to%20have%20an%20heir%20succeed%20them%20than%20founders%20with%20one%20child.%20What's%20more%2C%20research%20has%20found%20that%20only%20children%2C%20like%20first-born%20kids%2C%20tend%20to%20have%20a%20lower%20risk%20tolerance%20than%20younger%20siblings.%20China's%20one-child%20policy%20has%20contributed%20to%20a%20significant%20drop%20in%20the%20number%20of%20entrepreneurs%20%E2%80%94%20and%20only%20children%20who%20do%20start%20their%20own%20businesses%20tend%20to%20perform%20worse%20financially.%20One%20Chinese%20study%20found%20that%20companies%20run%20by%20only%20children%20generated%20revenue%20that%20was%2030%25%20lower%20than%20the%20revenue%20of%20companies%20run%20by%20children%20with%20siblings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOnlies%20are%20under%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.gse.harvard.edu%2Fideas%2Fed-magazine%2F10%2F05%2Fone-and-only%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20intense%20pressure%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20succeed%20professionally%20in%20part%20because%20of%20the%20financial%20burden%20they're%20expected%20to%20bear.%20They%20may%20start%20off%20life%20getting%20all%20the%20extra%20attention%20and%20devotion%20from%20their%20parents%20%E2%80%94%20but%20as%20their%20parents%20age%2C%20they'll%20be%20left%20alone%20to%20return%20the%20favor.%20Without%20any%20siblings%20to%20help%20out%2C%20only%20children%20face%20the%20prospect%20of%20being%20the%20sole%20caregiver%20for%20their%20parents.%20Studies%20suggest%20they're%20more%20likely%20than%20adults%20with%20siblings%20to%20provide%20direct%20care%20for%20their%20parents%2C%20such%20as%20bathing%20and%20dressing%20them%2C%20cleaning%20the%20house%2C%20and%20paying%20the%20bills.%20%26quot%3BI%20feel%20like%20the%20whole%20family%20rests%20on%20me%2C%26quot%3B%20Parker%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20baby%20in%20a%20crown%20as%20a%20CEO%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F672d02565ec9bfa3d63c6322%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EOnly%20kids%20are%20more%20likely%20than%20other%20kids%20to%20become%20CEOs.%20Thomas%20Edison%2C%20Jack%20Welch%2C%20Carl%20Icahn%20%E2%80%94%20all%20onlies.%3Cp%3EiStock%3B%20Rebecca%20Zisser%2FBI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20sense%2C%20having%20an%20only%20child%20effectively%20defers%20the%20costs%20of%20care%20by%20a%20generation.%20It's%20certainly%20cheaper%20to%20raise%20just%20one%20kid.%20But%20once%20that%20kid%20grows%20up%2C%20it's%20can%20be%20more%20expensive%20for%20them%20to%20care%20for%20two%20aging%20parents%20on%20one%20adult%20salary.%20And%20because%20their%20parents%20are%20likely%20to%20be%20older%2C%20many%20solo%20children%20are%20going%20to%20face%20elder-care%20questions%20earlier%20in%20their%20adulthood%2C%20while%20they're%20still%20trying%20to%20save%20up%20for%20a%20home%20or%20cover%20the%20costs%20of%20raising%20their%20own%20child.%20It's%20one%20of%20the%20few%20times%20that%20only%20children%20wind%20up%20longing%20for%20siblings.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20true%20that%20there's%20infighting%20between%20siblings%20when%20a%20parent%20dies%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Lyons%2C%20who%20lives%20with%20and%20remains%20close%20to%20her%20mother.%20%26quot%3BBut%20at%20least%20they%20can%20go%20through%20that%20experience%20together.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20one-child%20family%20has%20long%20been%20a%20stand-in%20for%20the%20best%20hopes%20and%20worst%20outcomes%20for%20the%20human%20race.%20In%201968%2C%20a%20Stanford%20entomologist%20named%20Paul%20Ehrlich%20and%20his%20wife%2C%20Anne%2C%20self-published%20a%20paperback%20titled%20%26quot%3BThe%20Population%20Bomb.%26quot%3B%3Cem%3E%20%3C%2Fem%3EThe%20Ehrlichs%2C%20who%20had%20one%20child%2C%20argued%20that%20the%20troubling%20headlines%20of%20their%20day%20%E2%80%94%20the%20Vietnam%20War%2C%20for%20example%2C%20or%20starvation%20in%20India%20%E2%80%94%20were%20all%20rooted%20in%20overpopulation.%20Unless%20we%20start%20having%20fewer%20babies%2C%20they%20argued%2C%20the%20planet%20is%20destined%20for%20famine%2C%20environmental%20degradation%2C%20and%20economic%20collapse.%20In%201998%2C%20the%20journalist%20Bill%20McKibben%20floated%20a%20similar%20argument%20in%20his%20book%20%26quot%3BMaybe%20One%2C%26quot%3B%20making%20an%20ecological%20case%20for%20smaller%20families.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFertility%20rates%20fell%2C%20and%20the%20population%20bomb%20never%20went%20off.%20These%20days%2C%20it's%20far%20more%20common%20to%20hear%20scaremongering%20about%20a%20population%20%3Cem%3Ebust%3C%2Fem%3E.%20America's%20most%20powerful%20billionaires%2C%20religious%20influencers%2C%20and%20conservative%20politicians%20are%20demanding%20we%20all%20make%20more%20babies.%20As%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fx.com%2Felonmusk%2Fstatus%2F1800318513502167246%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EElon%20Musk%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20father%20of%2012%2C%20said%20in%20June%2C%20%26quot%3BIt%20should%20be%20considered%20a%20national%20emergency%20to%20have%20kids.%26quot%3B%20Conservative%20authors%20publish%20books%20with%20titles%20like%20%26quot%3BWhat%20to%20Expect%20When%20No%20One's%20Expecting%3A%20America's%20Coming%20Demographic%20Disaster.%26quot%3B%20Vice%20President-elect%20JD%20Vance%20issued%20dire%20warnings%20about%20%26quot%3Bchildless%20cat%20ladies.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20as%20smaller%20families%20become%20the%20norm%2C%20the%20fears%20and%20stereotypes%20surrounding%20only%20children%20will%20inevitably%20subside.%20Just%20as%20having%20children%20is%20no%20longer%20seen%20as%20a%20required%20stage%20of%20adulthood%2C%20having%20siblings%20will%20no%20longer%20be%20a%20de%20facto%20part%20of%20childhood.%20Rainer%20Turim%20was%20raised%20in%20Manhattan%20as%20an%20only%20child%20who%20was%20immersed%20in%20his%20parents'%20adult%20world.%20%26quot%3BA%20lot%20of%20my%20friends%20in%20the%20neighborhood%20were%20older%20New%20Yorkers%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Turim%2C%20who's%2025%20and%20works%20in%20a%20restaurant.%20He%20has%20no%20idea%20how%20many%20of%20his%20classmates%20were%20also%20only%20children%2C%20because%20it%20never%20occurred%20to%20him%20to%20wonder%20about%20it.%20To%20him%2C%20it%20was%20totally%20unremarkable%20to%20grow%20up%20with%20no%20siblings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20of%20the%20millions%20of%20only%20children%20in%20the%20US%20will%20grow%20up%20to%20care%20for%20their%20parents%20on%20their%20own%2C%20build%20their%20own%20bonds%20of%20kinship%20and%20community%2C%20and%20lead%20their%20own%20companies%20in%20new%20and%20exciting%20ways.%20They'll%20spend%20much%20of%20their%20lives%20alone%2C%20as%20all%20Americans%20increasingly%20do%2C%20but%20they%20won't%20be%20lonely.%20And%20maybe%2C%20once%20there%20are%20enough%20of%20them%2C%20they'll%20no%20longer%20be%20seen%20as%20%26quot%3Bonly.%26quot%3B%20They'll%20just%20be%20%26quot%3Bchildren.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EAnn%20Friedman%20is%20a%20writer%20who%20lives%20in%20Los%20Angeles.%20She%20is%20the%20coauthor%20of%20%26quot%3BBig%20Friendship%3A%20How%20We%20Keep%20Each%20Other%20Close.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20orig