0Business%20Insider%20spoke%20with%20industry%20analysts%20to%20ask%20what%20should%20go%20right%20for%20Intel%20to%20get%20back%20on%20track.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIntel%20has%20specifically%20lagged%20in%20the%20age%20of%20generative%20AI%20compared%20to%20competitors%20like%20Nvidia%2C%20Qualcomm%2C%20and%20AMD%2C%20which%20have%20their%20chips%20produced%20by%20Taiwan-based%20chip%20giant%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftsmc-power-players-14-execs-leading-worlds-biggest-chipmaker-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETSMC%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBI's%20Alistair%20Barr%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fintel-qualcomm-odd-couple-wont-solve-us-chipmaking-woes-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epreviously%20wrote%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20since%20Intel%20is%20the%20only%20company%20manufacturing%20high-powered%20chips%20on%20American%20soil%20at%20scale%2C%20rather%20than%20outsourcing%20the%20job%20to%20Taiwan%2C%20the%20company%20is%20a%20key%20part%20of%20the%20bedrock%20of%20the%20country's%20technology%20ecosystem.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BChips%20power%20the%20modern%20economy%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20wrote.%20%26quot%3BIf%20you%20have%20to%20get%20these%20components%20overseas%2C%20you're%20vulnerable.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGiven%20lawmakers'%20keen%20geopolitical%20and%20economic%20interests%20in%20maintaining%20the%20US's%20technological%20advantage%2C%20that%20means%20weighing%20all%20possible%20outcomes%20for%20Intel's%20future%20as%20the%20company%20struggles%20to%20gain%20its%20footing%20in%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-china-new-technology-race-air-force-secretary-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAI%20race%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhat's%20going%20on%20in%20Intel%20is%20not%20good%2C%20and%20being%20removed%20from%20the%20Dow%20is%20just%20sort%20of%20the%20cherry%20on%20the%20sundae%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Stacy%20Rasgon%2C%20a%20senior%20analyst%20at%20Bernstein%20Research.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2282763c21-cb66-4baf-9c2f-d09417cdc772%5C%22%3EWhat%20needs%20to%20go%20right%3A%2018A%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIntel's%2018A%20process%20technology%20is%20key%20to%20its%20strategy%20and%20its%20next%20shot%20at%20a%20new%20process%20node%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fintel-roadmap-leadership-tsmc-samsung-analyst-skepticism-2025-2021-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eafter%20struggling%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20previous%20node%20upgrades.%20If%20the%20technology%20succeeds%2C%20Intel%20can%20win%20over%20customers%20and%20turn%20itself%20around.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIntel%20has%20executed%20five%20improved%20chip%20nodes%20in%20the%20last%20four%20years%2C%20resulting%20in%20smaller%20and%20more%20powerful%20transistors%2C%20%26quot%3Bwhich%20is%20a%20feat%20in%20itself%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Patrick%20Moorhead%2C%20CEO%20and%20chief%20analyst%20of%20Moor%20Insights%20and%20Strategy.%20Still%2C%20in%20recent%20years%2C%20Intel%20has%20failed%20to%20keep%20up%20with%20TSMC%20in%20the%20latest%20chip%20nodes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMoorhead%20added%20that%20Intel%20is%20investing%20to%20%26quot%3Bcatch%20up%26quot%3B%20to%20its%20competitors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIts%2018A%20node%20appears%20to%20be%20healthy%20and%20competitive%2C%20which%20is%20the%20key%20to%20its%20turnaround%20and%20the%20ability%20to%20recruit%20more%20foundry%20customers%2C%26quot%3B%20Moorhead%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIntel%20has%20announced%20Amazon%20as%20an%2018A%20customer%20so%20far.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20have%20to%20trust%20Intel%20to%20manufacture%20your%20chips%20on%20advanced%20processes%2C%20which%20they've%20just%20started%20adopting%2C%20efficiently%20and%20on%20time%20which%20they%20haven't%20done%20yet%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Logan%20Purk%2C%20a%20senior%20analyst%20at%20Edward%20Jones.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22053cf5c5-cc4a-47d6-b22d-74bd1e17888b%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EIntel%20needs%20to%20balance%20the%20books%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIntel%20plans%20to%20spin%20out%20its%20semiconductor%20manufacturing%20business%20into%20an%20independent%20subsidiary%20called%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fintel-ceo-pat-gelsinger-turnaround-plan-aws-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EIntel%20Foundry%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20separating%20the%20manufacturing%20process%20from%20its%20chip-design%20business.%20For%20this%20to%20work%2C%20the%20foundry%20business%20will%20need%20other%20major%20companies%2C%20including%20its%20rivals%2C%20to%20use%20Intel%20to%20manufacture%20their%20chip%20designs%20in%20large%20volumes.%20This%20hasn't%20happened%20yet.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOther%20chip%20companies%20that%20have%20separated%20their%20manufacturing%20and%20designing%20have%20succeeded%2C%20said%20Dan%20Morgan%2C%20a%20senior%20trust%20portfolio%20manager%20at%20Synovus.%20He%20pointed%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fintel-amd-nvidia-chip-manufacturing-moores-law-fabless-2020-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAMD%20spinning%20off%3C%2Fa%3E%20its%20manufacturing%20arm%20GlobalFoundries%20as%20an%20example%2C%20and%20he%20estimated%20that%20Intel's%20foundry%20business%20alone%20could%20be%20valued%20as%20high%20as%20%2480%20billion.%20Highlighting%20Intel's%20challenge%20here%2C%20GlobalFoundries%20only%20has%20a%20market%20cap%20of%20just%20%2424%20billion%20as%20of%20publication%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIntel%20CEO%20Pat%20Gelsinger%20has%20also%20said%20that%20Intel%20is%20making%20progress%20in%20cutting%20costs%20in%20their%20recent%20staff%20reductions%20and%20real%20estate%20sales.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBalance%20sheet%20is%20an%20area%20of%20focus%20for%20investors%20given%20the%20company's%20aggressive%20capex%20plan%20and%20ongoing%20losses%20in%20the%20foundry%20business%2C%26quot%3B%20Morgan%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERasgon%20said%20Intel%20is%20facing%20a