ou%20eat%20enough%20protein%2C%20Wright%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Feasy-calculate-how-much-protein-coach-olympians-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMike%20Molloy%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20nutrition%20coach%20to%20elite%20athletes%2C%20previously%20told%20BI%20that%20he%20advises%20people%20to%20eat%20about%200.75%20grams%20of%20protein%20per%20pound%20of%20total%20body%20mass%2C%20or%201.6%20grams%20per%20kilogram.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EProtein%20is%20a%20major%20component%20of%20bone%2C%20so%20it's%20important%20for%20building%20strong%20bones%2C%20too%2C%20Wright%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EVitamin%20D%2C%20which%20helps%20regulate%20the%20amount%20of%20calcium%20and%20phosphate%20in%20the%20body%2C%20is%20crucial%20for%20maintaining%20bone%20density%2C%20she%20said%2C%20so%20getting%20enough%20is%20vital.%20Most%20people%20get%20enough%20vitamin%20D%20from%20sunlight%2C%20but%20those%20living%20in%20colder%20climates%20are%20unlikely%20to%20get%20enough%20during%20winter%20and%20fall.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-you-have-to-eat-to-get-enough-vitamin-d-2019-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EVitamin%20D%20is%20found%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20a%20small%20number%20of%20foods%2C%20such%20as%20oily%20fish%2C%20red%20meat%2C%20and%20egg%20yolks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22945b42b7-9818-42d7-bd3d-a395ef4b83a3%5C%22%3ETake%20exercise%20micro-breaks%20from%20your%20desk%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMost%20of%20us%20spend%20our%20entire%20careers%20sitting%20at%20a%20desk%2010%20hours%20a%20day%2C%20which%20leads%20to%20muscle%20loss%20and%20an%20%26quot%3Bincredibly%20weak%26quot%3B%20musculoskeletal%20system%2C%20Wright%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20one%20of%20the%20hallmarks%20of%20aging%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20also%20linked%20to%20early%20death.%20A%202024%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ahajournals.org%2Fdoi%2F10.1161%2FJAHA.123.031156%5C%2