%20lyrics%20around%20placeholder%20words.%20Madhuri%20Dixit's%20dedicated%20rehearsals%20with%20choreographer%20Saroj%20Khan%20brought%20the%20song%20to%20life%2C%20filmed%20during%20a%20grueling%2025-hour%20shoot.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22TOI%20Entertainment%20Desk%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A2%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fhindi%2Fbollywood%2Fnews%2Ftezaab-turns-36-madhuri-dixit-shot-ek-do-teen-with-high-fever-composers-inspired-by-a-koli-tune-used-mukhda-as-dummy-placeholders-know-everything-about-the-blockbuster-song%2Farticleshow%2F115170721.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Chief%20Justice's%20Idol%3A%20Uncle%20Who%20Took%20On%20Indira%20Gandhi%2C%20Was%20Denied%20Top%20Post%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EForty-seven%20years%20before%20Justice%20Sanjiv%20Khanna%20took%20over%20as%20the%2051st%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20India%2C%20the%20Khanna%20family%20would%20have%20got%20its%20first%20chief%20justice%20in%20his%20uncle%20Justice%20Hans%20Raj%20Khanna.%20But%20a%20dissent%20judgment%20during%20the%20Emergency%20imposed%20by%20the%20Indira%20Gandhi%20government%20cost%20him%20the%20country's%20top%20legal%20post.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBorn%20in%201912%2C%20Justice%20Hans%20Raj%20Khanna%20completed%20his%20education%20in%20Amritsar%20and%20then%20started%20out%20as%20a%20lawyer.%20He%20was%20appointed%20district%20and%20sessions%20judge%20in%201952%20and%20later%20became%20a%20judge%20of%20high%20courts%20in%20Delhi%20and%20Punjab.%20He%20was%20appointed%20a%20Supreme%20Court%20judge%20in%201971%20and%20was%20in%20line%20for%20the%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20India%20post%20in%201977.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDestiny%2C%20however%2C%20had%20other%20plans.%20The%20Indira%20Gandhi%20government%20imposed%20the%20Emergency%20in%201975.%20In%201976%2C%20a%20five-judge%20Constitution%20bench%20heard%20the%20ADM%20Jabalpur%20vs%20Shivkant%20Shukla%20case%20and%20ruled%20that%20the%20right%20to%20personal%20liberty%20can%20be%20suspended%20in%20the%20interest%20of%20State.%20Justice%20Khanna%20was%20the%20sole%20dissenting%20judge%20in%20that%204%3A1%20verdict.%20The%20majority%20included%20then%20Chief%20Justice%20AN%20Ray%2C%20Justice%20MH%20Beg%2C%20Justice%20YV%20Chandrachud%20and%20Justice%20PN%20Bhagwati.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20his%20judgment%2C%20Justice%20Hans%20Raj%20Khanna%20said%20the%20law%20of%20preventive%20detention%20without%20trial%20%26quot%3Bis%20an%20anathema%20to%20all%20those%20who%20love%20personal%20liberty%26quot%3B.%20%26quot%3BSuch%20a%20law%20makes%20deep%20inroads%20into%20basic%20human%20freedoms%20which%20we%20all%20cherish%20and%20which%20occupy%20prime%20position%20among%20the%20higher%20values%20of%20life%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20wrote.%C2%A0Nine%20months%20after%20the%20judgment%2C%20the%20Indira%20Gandhi%20government%20appointed%20Justice%20Beg%20the%20Chief%20Justice%2C%20superseding%20Justice%20Khanna%20who%20was%20in%20the%20line%20for%20the%20top%20post.%20Justice%20Khanna%20resigned%20soon%20after.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnother%20key%20verdict%20Justice%20Khanna%20is%20known%20for%20is%20the%20Kesavananda%20Bharati%20v.%20State%20of%20Kerala%20judgment%20in%201973%20which%20saw%20a%2013-judge%20bench%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20outline%20the%20basic%20doctrine%20of%20the%20Constitution.%20In%20the%20landmark%20verdict%20passed%20by%20a%207-6%20majority%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20had%20asserted%20its%20right%20to%20strike%20down%20amendments%20that%20violated%20the%20fundamental%20architecture%20of%20the%20Constitution.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJustice%20Khanna%20wrote%20in%20his%20judgment%20that%20the%20Parliament%20had%20power%20to%20amend%20the%20Constitution%20but%20the%20basic%20structure%20should%20remain%20intact.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFollowing%20his%20resignation%20as%20a%20top%20court%20judge%2C%20Justice%20Hans%20Raj%20Khanna%20received%20a%20request%20from%20Janata%20Party%20to%20contest%20the%20elections.%20But%20he%20refused.%20When%20the%20Indira%20Gandhi%20government%20lost%20the%201977%20general%20election%2C%20the%20Janata%20Party%20approached%20him%20to%20head%20the%20probe%20panel%20investigating%20Emergency-related%20cases.%20Justice%20Khanna%20refused%20because%20he%20felt%20it%20he%20would%20appear%20biased.%20He%20held%20the%20post%20of%20the%20chairman%20of%20Law%20Commission%20from%201977%20to%201979%20without%20any%20pay.%20In%201979%2C%20the%20Charan%20Singh%20government%20named%20him%20Union%20Law%20Minister%2C%20but%20he%20resigned%20in%20three%20days.%20In%201982%2C%20he%20was%20the%20Opposition-backed%20candidate%20for%20President%2C%20but%20lost%20to%20Zail%20Singh.%20Justice%20Hans%20Raj%20Khanna%20was%20awarded%20the%20Padma%20Vibhushan%20in%201999.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJustice%20Hans%20Raj%20Khanna%20died%20in%202008.%20He%20was%2095.%20Nine%20years%20after%20his%20death%2C%20the%20ADM%20Jabalpur%20verdict%20was%20overruled%20by%20a%20nine-judge%20bench%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20in%20the%20Puttuswamy%20vs%20Union%20of%20India%20judgment.%20The%20bench%20noted%20that%20%26quot%3BJustice%20Khanna%20was%20right%20in%20holding%20that%20the%20recognition%20of%20the%20right%20to%20life%20and%20personal%20liberty%20under%20the%20Constitution%20does%20not%20denude%20the%20existence%20of%20that%20right%2C%20apart%20from%20it%20nor%20can%20there%20be%20a%20fatuous%20assumption%20that%20in%20adopting%20the%20Constitution%20the%20people%20of%20India%20surrendered%20the%20most%20precious%20aspects%20of%20the%20human%20persona%2C%20namely%2C%20life%2C%20liberty%20and%20freedom%20to%20the%20State%20on%20whose%20mercy%20these%20rights%20would%20depend%26quot%3B.%20It%20held%20that%20judgments%20by%20the%20four%20judges%20in%20the%20majority%20were%20%26quot%3Bseriously%20flawed%26quot%3B%20and%20that%20%26quot%3Blife%20and%20personal%20liberty%20are%20inalienable%20to%20human%20existence%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20Justice%20HR%20Khanna%20Inspired%20Nephew%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChief%20Justice%20of%20India%20Sanjiv%20Khanna's%20father%20Justice%20Dev%20Raj%20Khanna%20was%20a%20judge%20of%20Delhi%20High%20Court%20and%20his%20mother%20Saroj%20Khanna%20a%20professor.%20According%20to%20sources%20close%20to%20the%20family%2C%20the%20couple%20wanted%20their%20son%20to%20become%20a%20chartered%20accountant%20because%20a%20legal%20career%20had%20taller%20challenges.%20But%20the%20future%20Chief%20Justice%20was%20inspired%20by%20his%20uncle%20who%20had%20the%20courage%20to%20take%20on%20the%20State.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHe%20always%20considered%20his%20uncle%20an%20idol%20and%20used%20to%20keenly%20follow%20his%20work%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20source%20told%20NDTV.%20Chief%20Justice%20Sanjiv%20Khanna%20has%20preserved%20all%20the%20copies%20of%20Justice%20HR%20Khanna's%20judgments%2C%20his%20notes%20and%20registers%2C%20the%20source%20said.%20The%20judge%20plans%20to%20donate%20them%20to%20the%20Supreme%20Court's%20library%20when%20he%20retires.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202019%2C%20Justice%20Sanjiv%20Khanna's%20first%20day%20as%20a%20Supreme%20Court%20judge%20was%20in%20the%20courtroom%20his%20uncle%20once%20sat%20in.%20The%20room%20has%20a%20portrait%20of%20Justice%20HR%20Khanna%20and%20the%20Chief%20Justice%20plans%20to%20get%20a%20photograph%20clicked%20next%20to%20his%20inspiration's%20portrait%20before%20he%20retires.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1731312360000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-11%2Fkd939va8_cji-hans-raj-khanna-split_625x300_11_November_24.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fchief-justice-of-india-sanjiv-khanna-justice-hans-raj-khanna-chief-justices-idol-uncle-who-took-on-indira-gandhi-was-denied-top-post-6992215%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Forty-seven%20years%20before%20Justice%20Sanjiv%20Khanna%20took%20over%20as%20the%2051st%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20India%2C%20the%20Khanna%20family%20would%20have%20got%20